\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Compliance with this policy is mandatory for all Information Operations Personnel.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assessment
\series default
:
 Compliance with KB currency,
 Known Error publication timelines,
 Standard change procedure approval,
 annual review cadence,
 and documentation-before-closure obligations shall be assessed through the internal audit process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Internal Audits,
 Self-Assessment,
 and Control Testing) and the annual policy review and maturity scoring process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Annual Policy Review and Maturity Scoring).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Enforcement
\series default
:
 Failure to maintain required KB entries,
 publish Known Error entries within established timeframes,
 obtain required approvals for Standard change procedures,
 or document new procedures prior to work order closure shall be treated as non-compliance and may result in corrective action under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Policy Implementation,
 Enforcement,
 and Legal Alignment).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions to any requirement of this policy shall be documented in writing with a business justification and approved by the IT Director in accordance with the exception framework defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 No exception shall be granted on an open-ended basis;
 each exception shall specify a defined remediation timeline and any compensating measures in effect during the exception period.
 Oral exceptions are not valid.
\end_layout

