\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Documentation-Before-Closure Obligation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The assigned technician shall create or revise a KB article for any task executed without a corresponding KB entry prior to closing the associated work order.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Clarification
\series default
:
 Updating an existing KB article to cover a new variant of a documented procedure satisfies this obligation;
 a separate article is not required for every unique task instance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7 Review,
 Retirement,
 and Retention
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The following review,
 retirement,
 and retention obligations govern the lifecycle of all KB entries.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Review
\series default
:
 The content owner (Network Administrator or Systems Administrator as applicable) shall review each KB entry within their domain no less than annually or following any Significant or Emergency change affecting the documented procedure or reference artifact.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Retirement
\series default
:
 Only the IT Director shall authorize the formal retirement of any KB article.
 The Assistant IT Director shall mark retired articles as inactive upon IT Director authorization.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Retention
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall ensure that retired articles are retained in an inactive state for a minimum of six (6) calendar years after supersession or official abandonment,
 in accordance with NRS 239.125 and Nevada Local Government Records Retention Schedule LRDA 20070057.
 The IT Director shall not authorize disposition of any KB article subject to an active litigation hold,
 audit hold,
 or public records preservation requirement,
 regardless of the retention period.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Confidentiality
\series default
:
 All KB content shall be treated as operationally confidential.
 No Information Operations Personnel shall distribute KB content externally without written IT Director authorization.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Clarification
\series default
:
 This operational designation does not alter public records status or disclosure requirements under applicable law.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

